#### 4.3 Correlation Patterns (Methodological Note)

The correlation matrix produced perfect positive or negative correlations (+1.0 or -1.0) due to the two-document sample. While not generalizable, these results effectively illustrate the opposing rhetorical structures within this specific corpus. For instance, Dignity and Tribalism are perfectly negatively correlated. McCain's speech scores high on Dignity by extending respect to his opponent [4], while scoring low on Tribalism by framing political differences within a context of shared democratic process [5]. Conversely, Sanders' speech scores higher on Tribalism by identifying a specific antagonist group ("three Wall Street firms") [6], which is co-occurrent with high Resentment.

